%N A396292 In Glinski's hexagonal chess, these are the cells in the hexagonal spiral that can be reached by a Glinski queen placed at cell 0.
%C A396292 Note that, as in conventional chess, the earliest cells that a queen cannot reach (see A396293) are the same as the earliest cells that a knight /can/ reach (see A395362).
%H A396292 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A396292/b396292.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1639</a>
%H A396292 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A396292/a396292.jpg">The start of the hexagonal spiral. The red cells can be reached by a Glinski queen at cell 0; the blue cells can be reached by a Glinski knight at cell 0</a>
%Y A396292 This is the union of sequences A000567, A049450, A033428, A049451, A045944, A028896, A062783, A396288, A396289, A063436, A396290, and A396291.
%Y A396292 See A396293 for the complement. See also A395362 for the moves that can be made by a Glinski knight.
%K A396292 nonn
%O A396292 1,3
